Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: If you did that you could take away the incumbents' advantage because challengers like me would have a chance to run against incumbents like him for House races and Senate races, and then the voters could make up their own mind without being subject to an unfair fight.
Speech: If you did that you could take away the incumbents' advantage because challengers like me would have a chance to run against incumbents like him for House races and Senate races, and then the voters could make up their own mind without being subject to an unfair fight.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So that's how I feel about it, and I think if we had the right kind of campaign reform, we'd get the changes you want.
Speech: So that's how I feel about it, and I think if we had the right kind of campaign reform, we'd get the changes you want.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let me do first on a personal level.
Speech: Let me do first on a personal level.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If the American people send me up to do this job, I intend to be there one term.
Speech: If the American people send me up to do this job, I intend to be there one term.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I do not intend to spend one minute of one day thinking about re-election.
Speech: I do not intend to spend one minute of one day thinking about re-election.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And as a matter of principle -- and my situation is unique, and I understand it -- I would take absolutely no compensation; I go as their servant.
Speech: And as a matter of principle -- and my situation is unique, and I understand it -- I would take absolutely no compensation; I go as their servant.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Now, I have set as strong an example as I can, then at that point when we sit down over at Capitol Hill -- tomorrow night I'm going to be talking about government reform -- it's a long subject, you wouldn't let me finish tonight.
Speech: Now, I have set as strong an example as I can, then at that point when we sit down over at Capitol Hill -- tomorrow night I'm going to be talking about government reform -- it's a long subject, you wouldn't let me finish tonight.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If you want to hear it, you get it tomorrow night -- you'll hear it tomorrow night.
Speech: If you want to hear it, you get it tomorrow night -- you'll hear it tomorrow night.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: But we have got to reform government.
Speech: But we have got to reform government.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If you put term limits in and don't reform government, you won't get the benefits you thought.
Speech: If you put term limits in and don't reform government, you won't get the benefits you thought.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It takes both.
Speech: It takes both.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: So we need to do the reforms and the term limits.
Speech: So we need to do the reforms and the term limits.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And after we reform it, it won't be a lifetime career opportunity; good people will go serve and then go back to their homes and not become foreign lobbyists and cash in at 30,000 bucks a month and then take time off to run some president's campaign.
Speech: And after we reform it, it won't be a lifetime career opportunity; good people will go serve and then go back to their homes and not become foreign lobbyists and cash in at 30,000 bucks a month and then take time off to run some president's campaign.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: They're all nice people, they're just in a bad system.
Speech: They're all nice people, they're just in a bad system.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I don't think there are any villains, but, boy, is the system rotten.
Speech: I don't think there are any villains, but, boy, is the system rotten.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: I've had more people talk to me about their health care problems I guess than anything else, all across America -- you know, people who've lost their jobs, lost their businesses, had to give up their jobs because of sick children.
Speech: I've had more people talk to me about their health care problems I guess than anything else, all across America -- you know, people who've lost their jobs, lost their businesses, had to give up their jobs because of sick children.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So let me try to answer you in this way.
Speech: So let me try to answer you in this way.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let's start with a premise.
Speech: Let's start with a premise.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We spend 30% more of our income than any nation on earth on health care, and yet we insure fewer people.
Speech: We spend 30% more of our income than any nation on earth on health care, and yet we insure fewer people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have 35 million people without any insurance at all -- and I see them all the time.
Speech: We have 35 million people without any insurance at all -- and I see them all the time.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: A hundred thousand Americans a month have lost their health insurance just in the last 4 years.
Speech: A hundred thousand Americans a month have lost their health insurance just in the last 4 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So if you analyze where we're out of line with other countries, you come up with the following conclusions.
Speech: So if you analyze where we're out of line with other countries, you come up with the following conclusions.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number one, we spend at least $60 billion a year on insurance, administrative cost, bureaucracy, and government regulation that wouldn't be spent in any other nation.
Speech: Number one, we spend at least $60 billion a year on insurance, administrative cost, bureaucracy, and government regulation that wouldn't be spent in any other nation.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So we have to have, in my judgment, a drastic simplification of the basic health insurance policies of this country, be very comprehensive for everybody.
Speech: So we have to have, in my judgment, a drastic simplification of the basic health insurance policies of this country, be very comprehensive for everybody.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Employers would cover their employees, government would cover the unemployed.
Speech: Employers would cover their employees, government would cover the unemployed.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Number 2, I think you have to take on specifically the insurance companies and require them to make some significant change in the way they rate people in the big community pools.
Speech: Number 2, I think you have to take on specifically the insurance companies and require them to make some significant change in the way they rate people in the big community pools.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think you have to tell the pharmaceutical companies they can't keep raising drug prices at three times the rate of inflation.
Speech: I think you have to tell the pharmaceutical companies they can't keep raising drug prices at three times the rate of inflation.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think you have to take on medical fraud.
Speech: I think you have to take on medical fraud.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think you have to help doctors stop practicing defensive medicine.
Speech: I think you have to help doctors stop practicing defensive medicine.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I've recommended that our doctors be given a set of national practice guidelines and that if they follow those guidelines that raises the presumption that they didn't do anything wrong.
Speech: I've recommended that our doctors be given a set of national practice guidelines and that if they follow those guidelines that raises the presumption that they didn't do anything wrong.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think you have to have a system of primary and preventive clinics in our inner cities and our rural areas so people can have access to health care.
Speech: I think you have to have a system of primary and preventive clinics in our inner cities and our rural areas so people can have access to health care.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The key is to control the cost and maintain the quality.
Speech: The key is to control the cost and maintain the quality.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: To do that you need a system of managed competition where all of us are covered in big groups and we can choose our doctors and our hospitals, a wide range, but there is an incentive to control costs.
Speech: To do that you need a system of managed competition where all of us are covered in big groups and we can choose our doctors and our hospitals, a wide range, but there is an incentive to control costs.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I think there has to be -- I think Mr. Perot and I agree on this, there has to be a national commission of health care providers and health care consumers that set ceilings to keep health costs in line with inflation, plus population growth.
Speech: And I think there has to be -- I think Mr. Perot and I agree on this, there has to be a national commission of health care providers and health care consumers that set ceilings to keep health costs in line with inflation, plus population growth.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now, let me say, some people say we can't do this but Hawaii does it.
Speech: Now, let me say, some people say we can't do this but Hawaii does it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They cover 98% of their people and their insurance premiums are much cheaper than the rest of America, and so does Rochester, New York.
Speech: They cover 98% of their people and their insurance premiums are much cheaper than the rest of America, and so does Rochester, New York.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They now have a plan to cover everybody and their premiums are two-thirds of the rest of the country.
Speech: They now have a plan to cover everybody and their premiums are two-thirds of the rest of the country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: This is very important.
Speech: This is very important.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's a big human problem and a devastating economic problem for America, and I'm going to send a plan to do this within the first 100 days of my presidency.
Speech: It's a big human problem and a devastating economic problem for America, and I'm going to send a plan to do this within the first 100 days of my presidency.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's terribly important.
Speech: It's terribly important.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: I just have to say something.
Speech: I just have to say something.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I don't want to stampede.
Speech: I don't want to stampede.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Ross was very articulate across the country.
Speech: Ross was very articulate across the country.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I don't want anybody to stampede to cut the president's salary off altogether.
Speech: I don't want anybody to stampede to cut the president's salary off altogether.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Barbara's sitting over here and I -- but what I have proposed, 10% cut, downsize the government, and we can get that done.
Speech: Barbara's sitting over here and I -- but what I have proposed, 10% cut, downsize the government, and we can get that done.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: She asked a question, I think, is whether the health care profession was to blame.
Speech: She asked a question, I think, is whether the health care profession was to blame.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: No.
Speech: No.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: One thing to blame is these malpractice lawsuits.
Speech: One thing to blame is these malpractice lawsuits.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: They're breaking the system.
Speech: They're breaking the system.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It costs $20-25 billion a year, and I want to see those outrageous claims capped.
Speech: It costs $20-25 billion a year, and I want to see those outrageous claims capped.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Doctors don't dare to deliver babies sometimes because they're afraid that somebody's going to sue them.
Speech: Doctors don't dare to deliver babies sometimes because they're afraid that somebody's going to sue them.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: People don't dare -- medical practitioners, to help somebody along the highway that are hurt because they're afraid that some lawyer's going to come along and get a big lawsuit.
Speech: People don't dare -- medical practitioners, to help somebody along the highway that are hurt because they're afraid that some lawyer's going to come along and get a big lawsuit.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: So you can't blame the practitioners for the health problem.
Speech: So you can't blame the practitioners for the health problem.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And my program is this.
Speech: And my program is this.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Keep the government as far out of it as possible, make insurance available to the poorest of the poor, through vouchers, next range in the income bracket, through tax credits, and get on about the business of pooling insurance.
Speech: Keep the government as far out of it as possible, make insurance available to the poorest of the poor, through vouchers, next range in the income bracket, through tax credits, and get on about the business of pooling insurance.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: A great big company can buy -- Ross has got a good-sized company, been very successful.
Speech: A great big company can buy -- Ross has got a good-sized company, been very successful.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: He can buy insurance cheaper than Mom and Pop's store on the corner.
Speech: He can buy insurance cheaper than Mom and Pop's store on the corner.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But if those Mom and Pop stores all get together and pool, they too can bring the cost of insurance down.
Speech: But if those Mom and Pop stores all get together and pool, they too can bring the cost of insurance down.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: So I want to keep the quality of health care.
Speech: So I want to keep the quality of health care.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: That means keep government out of it.
Speech: That means keep government out of it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to do -- I don't like this idea of these boards.
Speech: I want to do -- I don't like this idea of these boards.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It all sounds to me like you're going to have some government setting price.
Speech: It all sounds to me like you're going to have some government setting price.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want competition and I want to pool the insurance and take care of it that way and have -- oh, here's the other point.
Speech: I want competition and I want to pool the insurance and take care of it that way and have -- oh, here's the other point.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I think medical care should go with the person.
Speech: I think medical care should go with the person.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: If you leave a business, I think your insurance should go with you to some other business.
Speech: If you leave a business, I think your insurance should go with you to some other business.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: You shouldn't be worrying if you get a new job as to whether that's gonna -- and part of our plan is to make it what they call portable -- big word, but that means if you're working for the Jones Company and you go to the Smith Company, your insurance goes with you.
Speech: You shouldn't be worrying if you get a new job as to whether that's gonna -- and part of our plan is to make it what they call portable -- big word, but that means if you're working for the Jones Company and you go to the Smith Company, your insurance goes with you.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I think it's a good program.
Speech: I think it's a good program.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I'm really excited about getting it done, too.
Speech: I'm really excited about getting it done, too.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: PEROT: We have the most expensive health care system in the world.
Speech: We have the most expensive health care system in the world.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Twelve percent of our gross national product goes to health care.
Speech: Twelve percent of our gross national product goes to health care.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Our industrial competitors, who are beating us in competition, spend less and have better health care.
Speech: Our industrial competitors, who are beating us in competition, spend less and have better health care.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Japan spends a little over 6% of its gross national product.
Speech: Japan spends a little over 6% of its gross national product.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Germany spends 8%.
Speech: Germany spends 8%.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It's fascinating.
Speech: It's fascinating.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You've bought a front row box seat and you're not happy with your health care and you're saying tonight we've got bad health care but very expensive health care.
Speech: You've bought a front row box seat and you're not happy with your health care and you're saying tonight we've got bad health care but very expensive health care.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Folks, here's why.
Speech: Folks, here's why.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Go home and look in the mirror.
Speech: Go home and look in the mirror.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You own this country but you have no voice in it the way it's organized now, and if you want to have a high risk experience, comparable to bungee jumping, go into Congress some time when they're working on this kind of legislation, when the lobbyists are running up and down the halls.
Speech: You own this country but you have no voice in it the way it's organized now, and if you want to have a high risk experience, comparable to bungee jumping, go into Congress some time when they're working on this kind of legislation, when the lobbyists are running up and down the halls.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Wear your safety toe shoes when you go.
Speech: Wear your safety toe shoes when you go.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And as a private citizen, believe me, you are looked on as a major nuisance.
Speech: And as a private citizen, believe me, you are looked on as a major nuisance.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: The facts are you now have a government that comes at you.
Speech: The facts are you now have a government that comes at you.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You're supposed to have a government that comes from you.
Speech: You're supposed to have a government that comes from you.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Now, there are all kinds of good ideas, brilliant ideas, terrific ideas on health care.
Speech: Now, there are all kinds of good ideas, brilliant ideas, terrific ideas on health care.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: None of them ever get implemented because -- let me give you an example.
Speech: None of them ever get implemented because -- let me give you an example.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: A senator runs every 6 years.
Speech: A senator runs every 6 years.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: He's got to raise 20,000 bucks a week to have enough money to run.
Speech: He's got to raise 20,000 bucks a week to have enough money to run.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Who's he gonna listen to -- us or the folks running up and down the aisles with money, the lobbyists, the PAC money?
Speech: Who's he gonna listen to -- us or the folks running up and down the aisles with money, the lobbyists, the PAC money?
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: He listens to them.
Speech: He listens to them.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Who do they represent?
Speech: Who do they represent?
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Health care industry.
Speech: Health care industry.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Not us.
Speech: Not us.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Now, you've got to have a government that comes from you again.
Speech: Now, you've got to have a government that comes from you again.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You've got to reassert your ownership in this country and you've got to completely reform our government.
Speech: You've got to reassert your ownership in this country and you've got to completely reform our government.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And at that point they'll just be like apples falling out of a tree.
Speech: And at that point they'll just be like apples falling out of a tree.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: The programs will be good because the elected officials will be listening to -- I said the other night I was all ears and I would listen to any good idea.
Speech: The programs will be good because the elected officials will be listening to -- I said the other night I was all ears and I would listen to any good idea.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I think we ought to do plastic surgery on a lot of these guys so that they're all ears, too, and listen to you.
Speech: I think we ought to do plastic surgery on a lot of these guys so that they're all ears, too, and listen to you.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Then you get what you want, and shouldn't you?
Speech: Then you get what you want, and shouldn't you?
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You paid for it.
Speech: You paid for it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Why shouldn't you get what you want, as opposed to what some lobbyist cuts a deal, writes a little piece in the law and he goes through.
Speech: Why shouldn't you get what you want, as opposed to what some lobbyist cuts a deal, writes a little piece in the law and he goes through.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: That's the way the game's played now.
Speech: That's the way the game's played now.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Till you change it you're gonna be unhappy.
Speech: Till you change it you're gonna be unhappy.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: One brief point.
Speech: One brief point.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have elections so people can make decisions about this.
Speech: We have elections so people can make decisions about this.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The point I want to make to you is, a bipartisan commission reviewed my plan and the Bush plan and there were as many Republicans as Democratic health care experts on it.
Speech: The point I want to make to you is, a bipartisan commission reviewed my plan and the Bush plan and there were as many Republicans as Democratic health care experts on it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They concluded that my plan would cover everybody and his would leave 27 million behind by the year 2000 and that my plan in the next 12 years would save $2.2 trillion in public and private money to reinvest in this economy and the average family would save $1200 a year under the plan that I offered without any erosion in the quality of health care.
Speech: They concluded that my plan would cover everybody and his would leave 27 million behind by the year 2000 and that my plan in the next 12 years would save $2.2 trillion in public and private money to reinvest in this economy and the average family would save $1200 a year under the plan that I offered without any erosion in the quality of health care.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I ask you to look at that.
Speech: So I ask you to look at that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And you have to vote for somebody with a plan.
Speech: And you have to vote for somebody with a plan.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what you have elections for.
Speech: That's what you have elections for.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: If people would say, well, he got elected to do this and then the Congress says, okay, I'm going to do it.
Speech: If people would say, well, he got elected to do this and then the Congress says, okay, I'm going to do it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what the election was about.
Speech: That's what the election was about.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton
